                <h1>Can Wallpaper Stick to Textured Walls? Tips & Tricks</h1>
                <p>Wallpaper can adhere to textured walls, but results vary based on wall texture and wallpaper type. If the texture is too pronounced, wallpaper may not stick well, leading to issues like peeling or bubbling. For best results, consider using peel-and-stick options or properly prep the surface to ensure a smoother application.</p>
